The paper deals with the integration of probabilistic modeling with first-order logic, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on knowledge discovery on RDF datasets, which is a subfield of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses state-of-the-art techniques for rule mining and inference computation, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the Semantic Web foundations, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
